       title="Initialise RBAM" id="Initialise-RBAM">

    <p>Before RBAM can be used, it must be initialised to setup its own access control.</p>
    <p>
        There is one Role - <code>Rbam</code> - which grants all RBAM Permissions.
        If this does not meet your requirements, use RBAM to add additional Roles and change the hierarchy
        after it has been initialised.
    </p>
    <warning>
        Do not change RBAM Permissions
    </warning>

    <p>The RBAM system is initialised using the <code>rbam:initialise</code> yii console command.</p>
    <p>
        Run <code>yii rbam:initialise UID</code><br/>
        where UID is the user ID to assign to the <code>Rbam</code> Role.
    </p>

    <p>Once initialised, RBAM cannot be initialised again without removing all Roles.</p>

